race.comment: FINAL MOMENT (7) jumped out well and resumed further improved beaten a nose at Sandown-Hillside over this distance. Will be fitter for the run and is a decent chance to go one better. GRAM (2) has switched from James Cummings to a top Victorian barn. Has been off the scene for 463 days, but his best is comfortably good enough for this. He's been gelded and has won both Mornington jumpouts. The late betting will be key. TASSORTING (6) is a local and has impressed at the jumpouts. Has the inside gate and the blinkers on and is ready to go. SAN PUEBLO (3) was plain last time but went well first-up at Moe prior on a heavy surface. Fitter and is suited with the cut out of the track.
